name: Constant Contact
description: Add a Constant Contact instance to connect your existing or new Constant Contact account to the Marketing Hub, allowing you to manage campaigns, lists, contacts etc. across multiple Marketing Elements. You will need your Constant Contact account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: New User
configuration.description: Use newUser=true to send users who do not have a Constant Contact account to the account signup page.

configuration.name: Max Page Size (or limit)
configuration.description: Constant Contact Max Page Size (or limit)

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON, an example of which is as follows - { "contacts": { "url": "/hubs/helpdesk/contacts", “idField”: “user.id”, “datesConfiguration”: { "updatedDateField": "user.updated_at", "updatedDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX", “createdDateField”: “user.created_at”, “createdDateFormat": "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssX" }, "pageSize": 10000 } }

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Search fields supported are: modified_since, status, (enum values: ALL, DRAFT, SENT, RUNNING or SCHEDULED). For example, to search for drafted campaigns:  status='DRAFT'

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The next page cursor, taken from the response header `elements-next-page-token`

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 50 if not provided. Maximum of 50

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Search fields supported are: email, modified_since, status, (enum values: ALL, UNCONFIRMED, ACTIVE, OPTOUT or REMOVED). For example, to query for a particular email:  email='amv@gmail.com'

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 200 if not provided. Maximum of 500

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: The next page cursor, taken from the response header `elements-next-page-token`

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression. Search field supported is: modified_since. For example, to query for lists modified since Feb 01, 2013:  modified_since='2013-02-01T17:54'

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size. Defaults to 200 if not provided. Maximum of 2000

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The page number. Defaults to 1 if not provided
